HEADWORD: Turret deck
<hw>Tur"ret deck</hw>. <def>A narrow superstructure running from stem to
stern on the upper deck of a steam cargo vessel having a rounded gunwale
and sides curved inward convexly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turreted</ent>⟦br⟧
